  "texts": [
    "Compared with Theorem 3, the reward optimality gap R-OPT(π ⋆ p (λ ⋆)) and the utility optimality gap U-OPT(π ⋆ p (λ ⋆)) do not depend on the conditioning of the dual function D(λ) due to the unique optimal dual variable λ ⋆.",
    "Similarly, when the parametrization gap ν is sufficiently small, the one-shot alignment instance of Algorithm 1 readily generates an approximate solution to Problem (U-CA).",
    "This appears to be the first optimality guarantee for the one-shot safety alignment [21].Having established the optimality analysis of Algorithm 1, we present a more practical version of it, accounting for randomness in the subgradient direction (6) and proximity in solving the LLM policy optimization (7), and establish the best-iterate convergence analysis; see Appendix B.10 for detail.",
    "Computational ExperimentsWe demonstrate the effectiveness of our iterative dual-based alignment method (referred to as multishot) through extensive experiments conducted on the PKU-SafeRLHF [23] and Anthropic HH-RLHF dataset [2] datasets, showing constraint satisfaction and trade-offs between reward and utility.",
    "We apply our method to a safety alignment task, aligning a pretrained LLM with human preferences to enhance its helpfulness while ensuring it satisfies a safety constraint with a given threshold b [23]."
